In this course the main concepts and basic theories of management and teamwork are covered. Participants learn to understand the main and associative functions of management by binding them with the individual differences of organizational members. In addition the basics of organizational design and its organizing with the principles of teamwork are unfolded. During the course participants learn to analyse different aspects of management functions with their applications, and implement them in a practical course of teamwork.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to create possibilities to gain basic knowledge of management and teamwork theories which allows understanding and solving important managerial questions.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course is passed the participant: * comprehends the management theories and can see how introduced theories apply in modern organizations management; * understands the content and the role of management in directing organizational activities, can estimate important aspects and issues of organizations management; * knows and distinguishes different management basic functions (planning, organizing, controlling, leadership, communication and decision making) and understands their essence on the assumption of management as a whole; * knows the main issues of organizational design and structure;  * understands management associative functions (communication, decision making) on the assumption of management as a whole; * is able to take into account persons' individual differences at the work place; * is familiar with the operation and analysis of the principles of teamwork; * are able to effectively participate in team work as a team member's position as well as a leader's.
